description.text:
Just Named One of the Top 25 Coolest Neighborhoods in the World! We will show you why this district earned such a prestigious award. 
Discover parts of East Austin that never made it in the guidebook on the ever changing street art scene on East Cesar Chavez. We will set out on a colorful walk full of murals, street art, and local art history in one of the edgiest parts of town. Together, we'll explore one of Austin's largest concentrations of public art. You'll see works by world-famous artists such as Blek le Rat, the French street artist who inspired Banksy, and hear real stories about the underground art scene in Austin! Reviews of this well curated tour focus on the tour guide's knowledge and passion of the artists and artwork.
 Whether you're looking for great photo ops, art history, or the inside scoop on local living in Austin, this art walk will touch on all of these subjects. As artists and lifelong residents of the Southwest, we will teach you how to decode what our city—and yours—is telling you every day. By the end of the walk, we guarantee you'll know more about Austin's public art than most local residents, and you'll never look at murals, street art, or graffiti the same way again. Plus, get a local perspective on Austin sights and travel tips from your guide along the way.
Check out www.atxartwalk.com for more info and reviews!

description.text:
You are invited to attend the Conception Art Show. A "pop-up" event presenting the work of 35 local artists.
- Live music
- Complimentary appetizer hour
- Cash bar
- Guests will have the opportunity to purchase something original for their home or workplace without incurring a gallery commission.
Conception Arts, founded in 2011 in NYC, hosts one-night 'pop-up' art events in 12 cities around the U.S. while additionally providing guidance and support for artists and makers looking to sell or promote their work, both online and in person.
"Bringing art to life in a way you can truly connect with is paramount to us here at Conception." - Conception Arts Co-founder, Rachel Wilkins explains.
"There are few other opportunities like this. The environment is unique and the art is wonderful" - Dallas Style & Design Magazine (September 2017 Issue)
"Must See" - Paper Magazine (2015)

name.text: Fine Arts Academy Audition & Portfolio Workshop Day 2019
name.html: Fine Arts Academy Audition & Portfolio Workshop Day 2019

description.text:
Who is this event for?
Prospective students and parents who reside within the AISD boundary and are applying to the McCallum Fine Arts Academy this year.
What will this event offer students?
Valuable instruction in preparation for the Fine Arts Academy application and audition or portfolio review with interview.  Students will be able to meet directly with faculty to not only get to know them but also learn where they should focus their preparation.  Workshops are student-only.  Click here for audition requirements.
What will this event offer parents?
A not-to-be-missed FREE information session about the Fine Arts Academy including specifics about each major, helpful application tips, and expectations of our Fine Arts Academy majors. Parent info sessions are held at the same time as the student workshops, which allows parents and students to acquire information simultaneously.  This is a popular opportunity to be able to ask all of your questions!
THREE Session Times:
9:00 a.m. - 10:00 a.m. and 10:10 a.m. - 11:10 a.m. and 11:20 a.m. - 12:20 p.m (if needed).
Students may register for 1 workshop in each session.  (Choose a different workshop for each session, since those workshops with the same topic will repeat.)
Session Locations:
Arrive in the MAC Theatre Lobby to sign-in.  Location and student guides will be available at that time.  Parent session is in MAC Theatre.
Workshops participation is not required and will not impact acceptance.  Registration is required at no-cost, and availability is first-come first-served. 
Parent session registration not required.

name.text: Premier Martial Arts Graduation Holiday Performance -  Sat Dec 14th 2019.
name.html: Premier Martial Arts Graduation Holiday Performance -  Sat Dec 14th 2019.

description.text:
Welcome to PMA'S last Graduation Ceremony of the Year - Saturday Dec 14th -2019.
NOTE: Location - Will be at Hopewell Middle School. Doors open - 4:45pm. Students in place 5pm. 5:10pm start.

PLEASE BE WEARING Uniform Pants, plus TEAM PREMIER T-Shirt. ALL FAMILIES purchased this shirt. We will have a handful of extra shirts, limited sizes that must be worn, for purchase at door. 

N/B: THERE IS NO CHARGE FOR FAMILY MEMBERS TO WATCH THE EVENT - REG FEE IS STRICHTLY FOR STUDENTS.


We are excited to see our students at this Graduation and for them to show you some of their skill sets.

Remember the Wed and Thursday 2 days before, is their Stripe Testing Day (All classes and stripes have been earned by this point). Graduation, belt CEREMONY is on Sat Dec 14th.

 IF FOR SOME REASON YOU ARE UNABLE TO ATTEND THE GRADAUTION CEREMONY - You/Your Child will be presented their belt and certificate the following week.
RED/BLACK will be performing on Tuesday the 17th if unable to attend.

VERY IMPORTANT: EVERY STUDENT MUST - Turn in completed Graduation form, regardless of taking part or not. 

Our goal is to help children become good human beings. Strong mentally, physically and emotionally.  
 
Graduation is for those children who have given satisfactory behavior at the martial arts school, their home, and school. All of which we have worked hard to stress the importance of setting a goal to achieve!
 
We can only see their progress at PMA. In the event you feel your child needs to work on any one of these areas please let us know so that we may work together to help your child be successful. 

*********     WE ARE EXPECTING ALL STUDENTS TO BE IN ATTENDANCE FOR THIS GRADUATION - Only students who started after November 17th will not be particpating.  *************
 
 

Please be sure your child has the following completed: 
 
-Turned in intent to promote form to PMA, signed by parent and teacher 
-Have all 3 Black Belt Excellence stripes from their BBE homework sheets (White belts will not - but must have 12 class min attendance).
-Have all 3 stripes from monthly stripe test 
- 16 stripes on belt for our Tiny Champs (3-4 yr olds)

**FORMS MUST BE TURNED IN BY THURSDAY 19th September (Forms are subject to late fee if past this date).
 
 
 
At testing please be sure to have:
 
Basic Students-
TEAM PMA TSHIRT and Uniform pants,
Gloves ON.
Shin Guards
 
BBT Students and Premier Level Students
Sparring Gear and Weapons. 


 
 
Thank you and we look forward to watching your child accomplish their next goal! 

NOTE      NOTE      NOTE:
Time slots will be filled as Grad forms are turned in, in the order they are received until each time slot is filled. 

When: Saturday December 14th 2019

Time: 5pm - 7pm.

Where: Hopewell Middle School

Who: All Students - All Ages.

name.text: ‘Beyond Breath’ - A free Introduction to The Happiness Program in Austin
name.html: ‘Beyond Breath’ - A free Introduction to The Happiness Program in Austin

description.text:
Discover the power of your breath to manage your mind and experience instant peace & calm.
Join a 90-minute free Workshop and get a glimpse of the Sudarshan KriyaTM- 
The breathing technique that is revolutionizing the lives of millions.

What you’ll discover at ‘Beyond Breath’
✔ A taste of the Sudarshan KriyaTM, a breathing technique taught in the Happiness Program
✔ An instant energy booster that awakens & relaxes your mind - Take it home and practice daily!
✔ The peace & calm of a unique guided meditation
✔ Secret keys to manage your mind
✔ The power of surrounding yourself with positive, like-minded people.

Master the Power of Breath to Transform your Life
No breath = No life 
What was the first act of our life? Breathing in.. 
What will be the last act of our life? Breathing out..
And in between is what we call life...

Every single day, we breathe in 10,000 liters of air!
Breath has the ability to purify our body, mind, and emotions - 
We eliminate 70% of toxins through the breath.
But we use only 30% of our lung capacity!

The quality of our life is determined by the way we breathe.
But learn nothing about our breath! 

You can use your breath to master your thoughts and emotions - the key to managing the quality of your day. Through the Sudarshan KriyaTM, a science-backed, rhythmic breathing technique taught in the Happiness Program, you can:


Tap into a reservoir of energy and use it as you please!


Relieve deep-rooted stresses and anxieties 


Uplevel your productivity


Overcome emotional blocks, move on from past events and shed limiting beliefs


Heal your body & gain power over your mind


Experience the true state of meditation



Learn more about the Happiness Program & the Sudarshan KriyaTM in our free workshop 'Beyond Breath'.


Please Note: To allow the best meditation environment for all, we kindly ask to avoid bringing children younger than 13 years to the event.
FAQs


How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Please contact us via email  kumar.bathala@artofliving.org or call 512-971-6052

This event is for kids at the age group of 8 to 17. 
Kids go through a lot of pressure in school and outside ... peer pressure, pressure of tests and homeworks and so on. This one hour session is dedicated to the kids to teach them simple tools and techniques to handle their negative emotions. They will learn how to be button proof, how to nourish human values and how to use breathing excercise as a tool to eliminate stress.
In this one hour workshop kids will learn:
✔︎Mindful awareness: How to become aware when negative emotion arises and become button proof. 
✔︎The power of breathing techniques - The quickest, most effective way to bring the mind to present moment.
✔︎ Insights into the nature of mind - How to relax mind and deal with negative thoughts and emotions
✔︎ Guided Meditation

description.text:
When: Every Friday 12:00 PM – 12:45 PM
Where: Premier Martial Arts 8400 Brodie Ln. Ste. 102 Austin, TX 78745
This 45 min class features mitt work to focus on your technique and speed. You will practice mitt holding and punching. ALL LEVELS WELCOME!
About this Event:
Do you struggle with Mitt Holding and want to improve? Are you a trainer who incorporates mitt work into your sessions? Do you want to ensure you and your partner gets the most out of their striking and mitt work? If the answer is yes to any of the questions above, this class is for you. We will cover basic and intermediate levels of holding and you will receive a great cardio workout. This class is free to our members and only a $10 drop in rate for non-members.
